casebody.head_matter:
Dawn BAKER, petitioner,
v.
Nancy A. BERRYHILL, Acting Commissioner of Social Security.
No. 18-5213.
Supreme Court of the United States
Feb. 25, 2019.
On petition for writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit. Motion of petitioner for leave to proceed in forma pauperis and petition for writ of certiorari granted. Judgment vacated, and case remanded to the United States Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit for further consideration in light of that court's opinion in Washington v. Commissioner of Social Security, 906 F.3d 1353 (C.A.11 2018).
